A civil society organisation, the Initiative for Leadership and Economic Watch in Nigeria (ILEWN) has hailed the acting chairman, Economic and Finance Crimes Commission (EFCC) Ibrahim Magu for  sustaining the fight against corruption in the country. This is even as the group stressed that the seemingly economic stability in the country can only be ascribed to the efforts from various quarters, including the EFCC. It said that EFCC remains the most vital organ of government when it comes to financial security. A statement made available to LEADERSHIP yesterday signed by the executive director, Amb Agbonkpolor Splendour also hailed the commission’s efforts towards ensuring checks and proper monitoring of financial transactions in the nation’s economy. The CSO said in line with international best practices the efforts of the EFCC in safeguarding the economy of the nation which has, in turn, brought about a robust economy, economic growth, and infrastructural development. It also noted that the credit also goes to President Muhammadu Buhari for counting Magu worthy to occupy the chairmanship position of the EFCC against all odds. The statement reads in part: ‘‘Those opposing the reappointment of Magu are riddled with negative motives inimical to the development of the nation. The CSO, therefore, called on President Buhari not to allow the naysayers to succeed in their evil ploy if Nigeria wants to sustain or surpass the present achievements in the fight against corruption.